context:
* The Arena Pitch Competition is a student entrepreneurship event hosted by George Brown College.
* The competition invites post-secondary students to showcase their business ideas throughout the month of March in 2024.
* There are 64 student entrepreneurs who will compete against each other in head-to-head brackets for the title of the nation's best.
* The application deadline is January 20, 2024, at 11:59 pm AT.
* Interested individuals can apply and sign up for college news and updates on the George Brown College website or contact ask.george@georgebrown.ca.
* The contact numbers provided are 416-415-2000 and TTY: 1-877-515-5559.
* The college's social media hub can also be visited for more information.
* Students are responsible for verifying the George Brown College fee requirements.
